data.name: Honey Garlic Shrimp with Rice
data.quickTastyDescription: Succulent shrimp glazed in a sweet and savory honey garlic sauce, served over fluffy rice for a delightful meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook rice according to package instructions and set aside.
In a bowl, mix honey, soy sauce, minced garlic, and ginger to create the sauce.
Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.
Add the shrimp to the pan and cook until they turn pink, about 3-4 minutes.
Pour the honey garlic sauce over the shrimp and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly.
Serve the shrimp over the cooked rice and garnish with sliced green onions.
data.modifiersForBase: Serve with rice for a complete meal.
